# Continuous integration

This project uses GitHub Actions for CI (see `.github/workflows/`).

## Codecov (optional)

The default CI workflow can upload coverage to [Codecov](https://about.codecov.io/). **Do not paste upload tokens into Copier answers or commit them to the repository.**

1. Enable the Codecov GitHub app or create a repository upload token in Codecov.
2. Add a repository secret named `CODECOV_TOKEN` under **Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions** in GitHub.
3. If you do not use Codecov, you can remove the upload step from `.github/workflows/ci.yml` or leave the secret empty (the workflow is configured not to fail CI when upload is skipped).

Coverage XML is produced as `coverage.xml` from pytest.
